To see if I understand bcrypt correctly, would this pseudo code achieve a similar adaptable computational cost?<p><pre><code>  function(uniqueSalt128Bit, password, rounds) {
    var hash = SHA1(uniqueSalt128Bit + password);
    var length = Math.pow(2, rounds);
    while (length--) hash = SHA1(hash);
    return hash;
  }</code></pre>
